-- Roth & Rau Slides Most Since 2008 in Germany After Earnings Decline 77%
-- B y   T o d d   W h i t e
-- 2010-11-10T10:13:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-10/roth-rau-slides-most-since-2008-in-germany-after-earnings-decline-77-.html
Roth & Rau AG  fell  as much as 12
percent in Frankfurt electronic trading after the German maker
of solar-cell production equipment said nine-month earnings
before interest and tax plunged 77 percent.  The stock dropped as much as 1.96 euros to 14.73 euros, the
biggest intraday percentage drop since December 2008, and was at
14.95 euros, down 10 percent, at 11:04 a.m. local time.  Hohenstein-based Roth & Rau said Ebit declined to 3 million
euros ($4.1 million) in the nine-month period from 13.1 million
euros a year earlier. Sales rose to 189.2 million euros from
159.5 million euros, the company said yesterday after the market
closed in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
